<paragraph blockId="36.[151,376,255,281]" box="[151,376,255,281]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,376,255,281]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,376,255,281]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Line 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hombron &amp; Jacquinot" box="[215,376,255,281]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[215,376,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,330,556]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation author="Laurent" box="[151,342,330,356]" firstAuthor="Laurent" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="10 - 14" refId="ref64098" refString="Laurent, R. F. (1995 a) A tentative arrangement of subgenera of the genus Liolaemus Wiegmann (Reptilia: Squamata: Tropiduridae). Bulletin of the Maryland Herpetological Society, 31, 10 - 14." type="journal article" year="1995" yearSuffix="a">Laurent (1995a)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the monotypic subgenus 
<emphasis box="[770,930,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Austroleamus</emphasis>
for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hombron &amp; Jacquinot" box="[984,1173,330,355]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis box="[984,1173,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which was therefore designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[357,407,370,396]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species). However, in later studies (
<emphasis box="[829,872,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge &amp; Espinoza" box="[879,1203,370,396]" firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref59521" refString="Etheridge, R &amp; Espinoza, R. E. (2000) Taxonomy of the Liolaeminae (Squamata: Iguania: Tropiduridae) and a semiannotated bibliography. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 126, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2000">Etheridge &amp; Espinoza 2000</bibRefCitation>
) it has been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[381,503,410,435]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[381,503,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Liolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Even though available evidence suggests that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hombron &amp; Jacquinot" box="[1067,1353,410,435]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis box="[1067,1353,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Liolaemus magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would represent a phylogenetically independent line within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[837,959,450,475]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,959,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Liolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus (see 
<figureCitation box="[1105,1179,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="61.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[416,1213,448,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-177@61.[340,1247,434,1696]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phylogenetic relationships between the Liolaemus species of the series signifer (subgenera Donosolaemus, Vilcunia and Eulaemus, and line magellanicus). The main structure of the tree is based on Schulte et al.’s (2000, 2004) and Espinoza et al.’s (2004) phylogenetic hypotheses. Additional details on phylogenetic relationships between species within each clade have been taken from specific phylogenetic studies (e.g. Avila et al. 2007; Pincheira-Donoso et al. 2007a)." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), additional evidence may be still required to recognize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laurent" authorityYear="1995" box="[556,716,490,515]" class="Reptilia" family="Squamata (awaiting allocation)" genus="Austrolaemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[556,716,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Austrolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid subgenus. Following a strict phylogenetic criteria, 
<emphasis box="[151,311,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Austroleamus</emphasis>
should indeed be validated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
